- VSCode Version: 1.8.0
- OS Version: Any

I am developing an extension which is activated when a folder is open in VSCode. Additionally I want to provide a boostrapping command, e.g. the user chooses an empty folder and my extension prepares all necessary files in this folder. Think of how you create a new C# project in regular VS - Class1.cs, Project.csproj and other files are automatically created.

I was thinking to use the vscode.openFolder command to let the user choose a folder to initialize. The problem is that if the user chooses an empty folder, my extension is no longer activated, unless I use activationEvent:* which I am quite reluctant to do.
If only after vscode.openFolder command I could run one last line of code in my extension, that would be great.

```javascript
vscode.commands.executeCommand('vscode.openFolder').then(folder => {
    if (folder) initializeFolder(folder);
    //bye-bye
}) ;
```

The problem is that the command promise is currently resolved immediately, but not when the user chose a folder (or cancelled the dialog).

VSCode Version: 1.8.1
OS Version: Linux (Ubuntu)

Steps to reproduce:
Enter this code into a .cc file:
```
int main() {
  os << (a? b->c(): d) << "#\n";
  const char* this_is_now_also_wrong = "??";
}
```

